body:
Here is the problematic code `test.v`:

```verilog
`timescale 1ns/1ps
module top (out12);
    reg signed [17:8] wire_1 = ~(6'o76);
    output wire  [19:10] out12;

    assign out12 = wire_1[10:10] ** wire_1;

    initial begin
      #1000;
      $display("wire: %b", wire_1);
      $display("out12: %b", out12);
      $finish;
    end

endmodule
```

The issue can be reproduced with the following commands:

```
iverilog test.v
./a.out
```

The output from Icarus Verilog is:

```
wire: 1111000001
out12: xxxxxxxxxx
```

However, since `wire_1` is `10'b1111000001`, we have `wire_1[10:10] = 1'b0`, so the expression `wire_1[10:10] ** wire_1` should evaluate to `0 ** wire_1`, which is `0`.

